  "text": "GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links. Razer just launched a new line of official Minecraft edition PC accessories, including new versions of the Razer BlackWidow V4 X mechanical keyboard, Kraken V4 X wired headset, Cobra wired mouse, and Gigantus V2 mouse pad. All four peripherals feature exclusive Minecraft-inspired color schemes and even come bundled with codes to unlock in-game items.While all four Razer x Minecraft items are available now, some are temporarily out of stock at Amazon. The good news is you can still add them to your cart and place them on backorder, and your order will ship once they're restocked. They're also available directly from Razer's online store and may also be in stock. Be sure to check all the links below to see if they're available. Razer BlackWidow V4 X Mechanical Gaming Keyboard - Minecraft Edition $170 The Minecraft edition of Razer's BlackWidow V4 X mechanical keyboard features doubleshot ABS keycaps with a color scheme based on the Creeper monster from the game, with green clicky switches and Chroma-RGB per-key backlighting. The board is also equipped with a few additional features, including six programmable macro keys, a multi-function roller, and media keys. You also get a key for the Ender Dragon Shawl in-game cosmetic item for Minecraft. Razer Kraken V4 X Wired Gaming Headset - Minecraft Edition $100 This version of the Razer Kraken V4X Wired gaming headset offers all the same specs and features of the standard edition--including 40mm drivers with 7.1 surround sound support, memory foam cushioning, a retractable cardioid mic, and Chroma RGB lighting--but sports a unique green and black color scheme, and comes packed with a code for the Ender Dragon Shawl in-game item. Razer Cobra Wired Gaming Mouse - Minecraft Edition $60 The Razer Cobra Gen3 is a lightweight, wired gaming mouse that features Chroma RGB lighting elements and Gen-3 optical mouse switches, which Razer says offers an extended 90-million click lifecycle and 0.2ms actuation time without debounce delay--in other words, clicks will be fast and accurate. Like the other items in Razer's new Minecraft accessory collection, it has a unique green color scheme inspired by the game with decals of the Greeper monster's face and comes with a key for the Overgrown Arm cosmetic item. Razer Gigantus V2 Cloth Gaming Mouse Pad (Medium) - Minecraft Edition $30 You can complete the collection with this Minecraft Edition oversized mouse pad with micro-weave cloth. It measures roughly 14 x 11 inches and is 3mm thick, with a high-density rubber anti-slip base. It's got a Minecraft skin that resembles the iconic dirt block from the game and is emblazoned with a Creeper face. It also includes a key to unlock the Overgrown Arm in-game item. The Biggest Upcoming Games That You Can Preorder Now SanDisk 1.5TB MicroSD Card Is Steeply Discounted At Amazon - Expand Your Steam Deck Storage Xbox Series X|S Owners Can Save Big On Western Digital's 1TB Expansion Card + Show More More Gaming, Tech, and Entertainment Deals \u0026 Preorders Links (5) Amazon-Exclusive Pokemon TCG Premium Collection Gets Huge Limited-Time Discount Lord Of The Rings Trilogy Limited Edition Steelbook Box Set Returns Next Month Nintendo Alarmo Now Available At Major Retailers - Mario Will Wake You Up For $100 New Nintendo Switch OLED Value Bundle Comes With Super Mario Bros. Wonder Final Fantasy X Magic: The Gathering Set Is Up For Preorder Brendan Hesse on Google+ Got a news tip or want to contact us directly? Email news@gamespot.com",
